<article class="menu-target7">
    <h3>Navbar</h3>

    <p>You can see 2 examples of Navbar up there & you can watch another with all the HTML code here on CodePen :</p>
    <a class="btn-black" href="https://codepen.io/animadio/pen/rRvxRe" title="Watch Navbar Example on CodePen" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">
        <i class="fab fa-codepen fa-lg" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        Navbar HTML
    </a>

    <p>There's no color classes for navbar because it's very easy to change any color you want with the custom properties...</p>
    <p>Same thing for fixed position or other properties (you can test to change every thing on CodePen directly)...</p>

    <p>The Navbar open-source code is available here :</p>
    <a class="btn-github" href="https://github.com/animadio/animadio/blob/master/src/elements/navbar.css" title="Watch the code on Github" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">
        <i class="fab fa-github fa-lg" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        Navbar CSS
    </a>

    <table class="table">
        <caption>Navbar Datas</caption>

        <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Class</th>
            <th>Property</th>
            <th><a href="{{ url('global') }}" title="How to use Variables ?">Variable</a></th>
            <th>@media</th>
            <th><a href="{{ url('grid') }}" title="How to Concat ?">Concat</a></th>
            <th><a href="{{ url('states') }}" title="How States work ?">States</a></th>
        </tr>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
        {% for navbar in allNavbarClasses %}
            <tr>
                <th>{{ navbar.class }}</th>
                <td>{{ navbar.property }}</td>
                <td>{{ navbar.variable }}</td>
                <td>{{ navbar.media|replace({'1': "yes", '0': "no"}) }}</td>
                <td>{{ navbar.concat|replace({'1': "yes", '0': "no"}) }}</td>
                <td>{{ navbar.state|replace({'1': "yes", '0': "no"}) }}</td>
            </tr>
        {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
    </table>
</article>
